5. Preprocessing Pipeline

In[6]:
numeric_cols = X_train.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns.tolist()
categorical_cols = [c for c in X_train.columns if c not in numeric_cols]

numeric_transformer = Pipeline(steps=[
    ("imputer", SimpleImputer(strategy="median")),
    ("scaler", StandardScaler())
])
categorical_transformer = Pipeline(steps=[
    ("imputer", SimpleImputer(strategy="most_frequent")),
    ("onehot", OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown="ignore", sparse_output=True))
])
preprocess = ColumnTransformer(
    transformers=[
        ("num", numeric_transformer, numeric_cols),
        ("cat", categorical_transformer, categorical_cols)
    ]
)

def evaluate_model(pipe, X_test, y_test, name, results_list):
    y_pred = pipe.predict(X_test)


    if hasattr(pipe.named_steps["clf"], "predict_proba"):
        y_proba = pipe.predict_proba(X_test)
        classes_sorted = np.unique(y_test)
        y_test_bin = label_binarize(y_test, classes=classes_sorted)
        auc_macro = roc_auc_score(y_test_bin, y_proba, multi_class="ovr", average="macro")
    else:
        y_proba, auc_macro = None, np.nan

    acc = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
    prec = precision_score(y_test, y_pred, average="macro", zero_division=0)
    rec = recall_score(y_test, y_pred, average="macro", zero_division=0)
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred, average="macro", zero_division=0)

    print(f"\n=== {name} ===")
    print(f"Accuracy: {acc:.3f}, Precision: {prec:.3f}, Recall: {rec:.3f}, F1: {f1:.3f}, ROC-AUC: {auc_macro:.3f}")
    print("\nClassification Report:")
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))


    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
    plt.figure()
    plt.imshow(cm, cmap="Blues")
    plt.title(f"Confusion Matrix  {name}")
    plt.xlabel("Predicted")
    plt.ylabel("Actual")
    for (i, j), v in np.ndenumerate(cm):
        plt.text(j, i, str(v), ha="center", va="center")
    plt.show()

    if y_proba is not None:
        RocCurveDisplay.from_predictions(y_test_bin.ravel(), y_proba.ravel())
        plt.title(f"ROC Curve  {name}")
        plt.show()

        PrecisionRecallDisplay.from_predictions(y_test_bin.ravel(), y_proba.ravel())
        plt.title(f"Precision-Recall Curve  {name}")
        plt.show()

    results_list.append({
        "model": name,
        "accuracy": acc,
        "precision": prec,
        "recall": rec,
        "f1": f1,
        "roc_auc": auc_macro
    })

def get_prob_scores(model, X):
    """
    Returns class-probability-like scores for multiclass ROC-AUC.
    Tries predict_proba, then decision_function (converted).
    """
    if hasattr(model, "predict_proba"):
        scores = model.predict_proba(X)

        if isinstance(scores, list):
            scores = np.vstack([s[:, 1] for s in scores]).T
        return scores
    elif hasattr(model, "decision_function"):
        scores = model.decision_function(X)

        if scores.ndim == 1:
            scores = np.vstack([1 - scores, scores]).T
        return scores
    else:
        raise ValueError("Model has neither predict_proba nor decision_function.")

def evaluate_models(models, X_test, y_test):
    """
    Builds a metrics table for each model:
    Accuracy, Precision_macro, Recall_macro, F1_macro, ROC_AUC_macro
    """
    lb = LabelBinarizer()
    y_test_bin = lb.fit_transform(y_test)

    rows = []
    for name, model in models.items():
        # Predictions
        y_pred = model.predict(X_test)

        # Basic metrics
        acc = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
        prec, rec, f1, _ = precision_recall_fscore_support(
            y_test, y_pred, average="macro", zero_division=0
        )

        # ROC-AUC (macro, one-vs-rest)
        try:
            y_score = get_prob_scores(model, X_test)
            # If LabelBinarizer produced a single column (rare), fix to 2 cols
            if y_score.ndim == 1:
                y_score = np.vstack([1 - y_score, y_score]).T
            # Align shapes for multiclass
            if y_test_bin.ndim == 1:
                # Binary case; make it 2D
                y_test_bin2 = np.vstack([1 - y_test_bin, y_test_bin]).T
                auc_macro = roc_auc_score(y_test_bin2, y_score, average="macro", multi_class="ovr")
            else:
                auc_macro = roc_auc_score(y_test_bin, y_score, average="macro", multi_class="ovr")
        except Exception as e:
            auc_macro = np.nan  # fallback if model cannot produce scores

        rows.append({
            "Model": name,
            "Accuracy": round(acc, 4),
            "Precision_macro": round(prec, 4),
            "Recall_macro": round(rec, 4),
            "F1_macro": round(f1, 4),
            "ROC_AUC_macro": round(auc_macro, 4) if not np.isnan(auc_macro) else np.nan
        })

    df_metrics = pd.DataFrame(rows).sort_values(by=["F1_macro", "ROC_AUC_macro"], ascending=False)
    return df_metrics

# Figure 4.7: ROC curves (macro-AUC) for each model
from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, auc

classes = np.unique(y_test)
lb = LabelBinarizer()
y_test_bin = lb.fit_transform(y_test)

def macro_roc_auc(model, X_test, y_test_bin):
    """Compute macro-average ROC for a fitted multiclass model."""

    if hasattr(model, "predict_proba"):
        y_score = model.predict_proba(X_test)
    elif hasattr(model, "decision_function"):

        scores = model.decision_function(X_test)

        y_score = scores if scores.ndim > 1 else np.vstack([1-scores, scores]).T
    else:

        raise ValueError("Model does not support probability/decision_function.")

    if y_score.ndim == 1:
        y_score = np.vstack([1 - y_score, y_score]).T

    fpr_list, tpr_list, auc_list = [], [], []
    n_classes = y_test_bin.shape[1]
    for i in range(n_classes):
        fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test_bin[:, i], y_score[:, i])
        fpr_list.append(fpr); tpr_list.append(tpr)
        auc_list.append(auc(fpr, tpr))

    all_fpr = np.unique(np.concatenate([f for f in fpr_list]))
    mean_tpr = np.zeros_like(all_fpr)
    for i in range(n_classes):
        mean_tpr += np.interp(all_fpr, fpr_list[i], tpr_list[i])
    mean_tpr /= n_classes
    macro_auc = auc(all_fpr, mean_tpr)
    return all_fpr, mean_tpr, macro_auc

def plot_feature_importance(pipe, feature_names, title, filename, top_n=15):
    # Access the classifier from the pipeline
    model = pipe.named_steps["clf"]
    if not hasattr(model, "feature_importances_"):
        raise ValueError("Model has no feature_importances_.")
    imp = pd.Series(model.feature_importances_, index=feature_names).sort_values(ascending=False).head(top_n)
    plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
    imp.iloc[::-1].plot(kind="barh")
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel("Importance")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(filename, dpi=300, bbox_inches="tight")
    plt.show()

feature_names = X.columns

if rf_key is not None:
    plot_feature_importance(models[rf_key], feature_names,
                            "Figure 4.9a: Top Feature Importances (Random Forest)",
                            "outputs/figures/Figure_4_9a_FeatureImportance_RF.png")

if gb_key is not None:
    plot_feature_importance(models[gb_key], feature_names,
                            "Figure 4.9b: Top Feature Importances (Gradient Boosting)",
                            "outputs/figures/Figure_4_9b_FeatureImportance_GB.png")
